        "text": "Sagan presents a set of tools for skeptical thinking which he calls the \"baloney detection kit\" (page 210f).[ The Demon-Haunted World: Science As a Candle in the Dark][ The Demon-Haunted World: Science As a Candle in the Dark] Skeptical thinking consists both of constructing a reasoned argument and recognizing a fallacious ([[fallacy]]) or [[fraudulent]] one. In order to identify a [[fallacious argument]], Sagan suggests employing such tools as independent confirmation of facts, debate, development of different hypotheses, quantification, the use of [[Occam's razor]], and the possibility of falsification ([[Falsifiability]]). Sagan's \"baloney detection kit\" also provides tools for detecting \"the most common fallacies of logic and rhetoric\", such as [[argument from authority]] and statistics of small numbers ([[hasty generalization]]). Through these tools, Sagan argues the benefits of a critical mind and the self-correcting nature of science can take place.",
